As RICKI wrote to Dr. Math
On 09/20/2004 at 23:51:59 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>I HAVE BEEN RACKING MY BRAINS TRYING TO DECIDE HOW TO APPROACH THIS 
>PROBLEM.  IF YOU HAVE 100 UNIQUE COMBINATIONS OF DOUBLE SCOOP ICE 
>CREAM CONES, HOW MANY FLAVORS WOULD YOU HAVE TO HAVE?


Since you could have 2 scoops of the same flavour the answer they 
want is almost certainly 10^2 = 100.  This means that 10 flavours 
would give you 100 different possibilities.  In this situation the 
order of the scoops matters.


>
>I TRIED 14C2 BUT IF IM DOING IT CORRECTLY IT RESULTS IN 91 
